  "description": "King Tubby at the bottom of the ocean. Filter cutoff at 200 Hz with resonance at 0.45 — the exact spectral profile of a dub bass cabinet. Sub octave mix at 0.55 reinforces the fundamental with weight. Pressure at 0.65 creates the compression character of tape saturation. The WRECK macro at 0.3 adds just enough cave body to simulate room reflections. Reverb at 0.25 — dub space, not ambient wash. Play notes in the C1-C2 range for foundation that displaces air.",
